    "content": "Mahmoud Ali Youssouf, the Chairperson of the African Union Commission, has called on international partners to reinforce support for the African Union Support and Stabilization Mission in Somalia (AUSSOM). Speaking about the mission's future, Youssouf emphasized the need for sustained funding and logistical assistance to maintain security gains in Somalia.\n\nThe appeal comes amid evolving security dynamics in the Horn of Africa, where Somali forces are gradually taking over primary security responsibilities from AU troops. The AUSSOM mission is a successor to previous AU operations, including AMISOM, and is tasked with supporting Somali forces in their fight against Al-Shabaab.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, the stability of Somalia directly affects the potential for safe return visits, investment, and the preservation of cultural ties. A strong AUSSOM presence is seen as crucial in preventing a security vacuum that could lead to renewed conflict and displacement.\n\nThe Chair's statement also highlighted the importance of predictable funding for the mission, as donor fatigue and competing global crises have strained resources. Youssouf urged member states and the United Nations to ensure AUSSOM remains well-equipped and capable of meeting its objectives.\n\nDespite recent progress in reclaiming territory from Al-Shabaab, the group continues to launch attacks in Mogadishu and rural areas. Analysts note that a premature withdrawal of AU forces could unravel gains made over the past decade, leading to increased instability and migration.\n\nRead the original report from Horseed Media here: https://horseedmedia.net/guddoomiyaha-midowga-afrika-oo-ku-baaqay-in-la-xoojiyo-taageerada-howlgalka-aussom/423550/",
